'''Johnny Carroll''' (born 11 May 1923)<ref name="whustats">{{cite web | url=http://www.westhamstats.info/westham.php?west=2&ham=116&united=Johnny_Carroll| title=Welcome to the Wonderful World of West Ham United Statistics&nbsp;— Johnny Carroll | publisher=www.westhamstats.info | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> is an Irish former [[association football|football]] player who played as a [[centre-forward]] for [[Limerick F.C.|Limerick]], [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] and [[Corby Town F.C.|Corby Town]].

==Footballing career==
Born in [[Limerick]], [[Ireland]], Carroll played for Limerick before signing for West Ham in 1948 along with his fellow countrymen, [[Danny McGowan]] and [[Fred Kearns]]. He made his debut against [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]] on 30 August 1948. Carroll played only five times in his West Ham career in all competitions without scoring. In 1949 he moved to Corby Town.<ref>{{cite book | title=Who's Who of West Ham United | publisher=Independent UK Sports Publications | author=Hogg, Tony | year=1995 | location=London | pages=41 | isbn=1-899429-01-8}}</ref>

